Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Pop the @diced chicken thigh{520%g} on a #baking tray{}. Put the broccoli on another. Sprinkle the @curry powder{} over both, then drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Pop the chicken tray on the top shelf and the broccoli on the middle shelf of the oven. Roast until the chicken is cooked and the broccoli tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

In the meantime, peel and grate your @ginger{1} and @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and half the @lime{1}. Chop the @tomato{2%medium} into small pieces. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Once hot, pop the garlic and ginger into the pan. Cook for ~{2%minutes}, stirring occasionally, then pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly reduced and thickened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @peanut butter{1} into the pan and stir to melt.

Once everything in the oven is cooked, set aside 2 portions of the chicken and broccoli (this will be for your lunch). Pop the remainder into the curry base, along with some of the cooking juices. Gently stir the curry, then season to taste with salt and pepper. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide it between your plates. Spoon the peanut butter chicken curry on top, pop a wedge of lime on the side. Dig in!

== Salad ==

Mix the @mango chutney{40%g} and juice from the remaining lime in a small #bowl{}, add @olive oil{1%tbsp} per person and season to taste with salt and pepper. Pop the lentils, tomatoes, lime zest, @wild rocket{40%g}, @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped) and remaining broccoli and chicken in a bowl. Toss to combine. Divide the dressing between your #lunch boxes{} and refrigerate. When ready to eat, mix together and enjoy hot or cold! Enjoy!